### CHAPTER XXXV.

1\. The thirty-fifth subject is this, that, when they wish to wash the
face <span id="fr_1273"></span>[1](#fn_1263.md), they *should* recite ore
Ashem-vohû <span id="fr_1274"></span>[2](#fn_1264.md), *and* set the mouth
firmly closed, so that the water, not staying *away* from it <span
id="fr_1275"></span>[3](#fn_1265.md), *shall* not go into the mouth. 2.
*And*, as *one* washes over the face, they *should* recite the
K*e*m-nâ-mazdâ <span id="fr_1276"></span>[4](#fn_1266.md), so that the
fiend Nasru*s*t <span id="fr_1277"></span>[5](#fn_1267.md) *may* become
smitten.

